{{Infobox museum | name = Philadelphia Museum of Jewish Art | image = | imagesize = | caption = | alt = | map_type = Philadelphia | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = Location within Philadelphia | coordinates = {{coord|39.96383|-75.16068|region:US-PA|display=inline,title}} | established = | location = {{Start date|1975}} | type = | accreditation = | key_holdings = | collections = | collection = | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | owner = | publictransit = [[File:SEPTA text.svg|20px]] {{color box|#{{SEPTA color|Market-Frankford}}}} [[Spring Garden (SEPTA Market–Frankford Line station)|Spring Garden]] | car_park = | network = | website = {{URL|http://www.rodephshalom.org/pmja/}} }} '''The Philadelphia Museum of Jewish Art''',<ref>[http://www.rodephshalom.org/pmja/ The Philadelphia Museum of Jewish Art]</ref> founded in 1975, located within historic [[Congregation Rodeph Shalom (Philadelphia)|Congregation Rodeph Shalom]], is dedicated to exhibiting contemporary art that illuminates the Jewish experience. The museum has organized solo and group exhibitions of work in many mediums by artists of diverse backgrounds.
